<html>
<head>
	<title></title>
</head>
<body style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: #f6f6f6; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; height: auto; min-height: auto;">
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color: #f6f6f6; padding: 10px;" width="100%">
	
		<tr>
			<td align="center" bgcolor="#f6f6f6">
			<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color:#ffffff; width: 600px;">
				
					<tr>
						<td style="padding: 0; background-color: #ffffff;"><img alt="Alliance Rural &amp; Remote - Email header (2)" src="https://allianceaustralia--uat.sandbox.file.force.com/file-asset-public/Alliance_Rural_Remote_Email_heade?oid=00DAD00000BK4sL" style="max-width: 683.05px" title="Alliance Rural &amp; Remote - Email header (2)" /><a href="https://www.alliancenursing.com.au"> </a></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td style="height: 30px;">&nbsp;</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td align="left" style="padding: 0 45px;">
						<p><b><span style="color:#3498db;">PLEASE CONFIRM YOU HAVE RECEIVED THIS INFORMATION VIA REPLY EMAIL.</span></b><br />
						<br />
						Hi {{{Recipient.FirstName}}},</p>

						<p>Congratulations on your contract at Central Australia Health Service. If you could please send us a brief message to let us know once you have arrived on location safely, it would be appreciated. 😊<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Attached please find your travel information.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						The address for the CAHS office is the Peter Sitzler Building, North Stuart Highway and their phone number is <a href="tel:0061889517808">08 8951 7808</a>.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						On Monday, «Date» please present to the CAHS office, at 0800 hours, at the above address. They will let you know where you need to go on Tuesday and Wednesday. Your Orientation will be conducted across these 3 days.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						On «Thursday/Monday» morning you will be collected from the hotel and taken out to the clinic, the driver will pick you up around 0830. You need to arrange for your groceries and supplies before this. (See below for options) If you have not been collected by 0900, please call the CAHS office to let them know you weren’t collected – sometimes the drivers can be delayed.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Please be aware of the following information:<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						<span style="color:#3498db;"><strong>Orientation Checklist&nbsp;– To be returned within 48hrs of commencing your contract</strong></span><br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Click on this link to complete the orientation checklist online: <a href="https://forms.office.com/r/4UNFTtYsZB">https://forms.office.com/r/4UNFTtYsZB</a><br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						The Orientation Checklist is not just a tool to assist in orientating you to your new work environment effectively, it also flags for you and us if there are any Occupational Health &amp; Safety issues that we need to address in order to&nbsp;make your work environment safe for you. Please assist us to support you as best we can by returning this form.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						<strong>Important Reminder – Pre-Risk Assessments – Document attached</strong><br />
						The completion rate for pre-risk assessments has dropped to just 3%. This is both concerning and unacceptable.<br />
						Your safety is our top priority. Completing a pre-risk assessment is not optional — it is a mandatory requirement&nbsp;to ensure risks are identified and managed before any call-out.<br />
						<br />
						<strong>What you need to know:</strong></p>

						<ul>
							<li>A pre-risk assessment must be completed before every call-out.</li>
							<li>Assessments must be uploaded</li>
							<li>No call-out is to proceed without a completed form.</li>
							<li>Compliance is expected to be 100% at all times.</li>
						</ul>

						<p>We will be monitoring completion rates closely. Results will be reported regularly and broken down by region so that areas of low compliance can be addressed.&nbsp;The Clinical Education Team will continue to support you with this process during community visits. Work is also underway on a PCIS service item to make completion easier — updates will be shared once available.&nbsp;Your safety matters — completing the pre-risk assessment each time helps protect you and your colleague<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						<strong>Alliance Rural &amp; Remote Health Emergency contact information:</strong><br />
						Office hours number: <a href="tel:0749985550">07 4998 5550</a> (QLD Time)<br />
						Afterhours Mobile: <a href="tel:0419716809">0419 716 809</a> – This number can be located on your ID Badge.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						We ask that you only use the <strong>Afterhours</strong> mobile number for urgent situations that cannot wait until the next business day.<br />
						&nbsp;</p>

						<ul>
							<li><strong>Incidents/Statements – IMPORTANT!</strong> If an incident occurs whilst you are on contract, you must notify us of the events that happened as soon as possible.</li>
							<li>Under the provisions of our Professional Indemnity Insurance, you are only covered if our Insurer is notified that an incident has arisen.</li>
							<li>Under the provisions of our Indemnity Insurance, we are required to view any signed statements prior to you providing it to a third party.</li>
							<li>You also must have your name badge and NT Working with Children’s Card&nbsp;on your person at all times whilst in the community.</li>
						</ul>

						<p><strong>Buddy Bonus Details</strong><br />
						Simply refer your Nursing friends or Nurses you meet whilst on contract, and when your referral applies with us, ask them to tell us your name. We then pay you a bonus on completion of your buddy’s first contract!<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Please note&nbsp;– Telstra is often the only mobile service available across most of remote Australia. Please check the following coverage maps to see that area you will be travelling to –<br />
						<a href="https://www.telstra.com.au/coverage-networks/our-coverage">https://www.telstra.com.au/coverage-networks/our-coverage</a><br />
						<a href="https://www.optus.com.au/about/network/coverage">https://www.optus.com.au/about/network/coverage</a><br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						<strong>PLEASE NOTE THE FOLLOWING REQUEST FROM CAHS:</strong><br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						CAHS drivers have massive days with some of the trips they do out and back and so they want to get away as early as they can. Our drivers have to&nbsp;adhere the departmental policy of being off the road by 6pm (dark) and if they don’t get away on time in the morning then they hit problems.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Can you please ask your RNs to do their grocery shopping prior to the morning they are leaving Alice Springs for the community?<br />
						If they want to buy groceries in Alice Springs rather than at community&nbsp;can they be encouraged to:</p>

						<ul>
							<li>Shop the night before and take it back to your accommodation.</li>
							<li>Preferred option&nbsp;is to ‘Click and Collect’ and to be collected as soon as the driver picks them up from the hotel. The order is to be arranged for 8.30am pick up at the supermarket.</li>
							<li>They can go to the supermarket earlier than 8.15am, let us know where they are shopping and they can be picked up from front of store - We will require permission to provide CAHS drivers with your mobile numbers if this is the case and you will need to be ready to be picked up from the supermarket by 8.30am.</li>
							<li>ONLINE ORDERS WITH COLES – CLICK AND COLLECT HAS TO BE DONE 4 (FOUR) DAYS PRIOR TO THE DATE OF COLLECTION.</li>
							<li>Coles have advised the best option is to call their customer care on <a href="tel:1800455400">1800 455 400</a>&nbsp;and the staff will be help you set up an account for your shopping.</li>
						</ul>

						<p>&nbsp;<br />
						<strong>Travel by Air:</strong><br />
						Please be aware if you are travelling with any of the Regional and Remote airlines that your baggage allowance will be SMALL. Please refer to the airlines&nbsp;website for your baggage allowance. It is your responsibility to pay any costs associated with excess baggage&nbsp;if&nbsp;the airline allows you to take the excess baggage with you.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> If your flight has been cancelled or delayed and there is a possibility that you will miss a connecting flight with a different airline, immediately call our office during business hours or our Emergency&nbsp;number <a href="tel:0419716809">0419 716 809</a> afterhours only. If we are not made aware of the situation with sufficient time to amend the travel arrangements, it will be your responsibility to pay for a new flight or any additional expenses that are incurred.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						If you have any further questions, please do not hesitate to contact me on the number below or via email.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Travel Safely.<br />
						&nbsp;<br />
						Kind regards,<br />
						{{{Sender.FirstName}}}&nbsp;{{{Sender.LastName}}}<br />
						Alliance Rural &amp; Remote Health</p>
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td style="height: 20px;">&nbsp;</td>
